<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-01-07T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-01-07T03:00:00-05:00" n="787" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d787">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">Nanking Embassy Files, Lot F79, 820
                            Surplus Property: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Josselyn</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Embassy in China</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-01-07T16:00:00+08:00">January 7,
                                    1946—4 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>5. From Johnson, Foreign Liquidation Commission, Shanghai. <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“Soong has stated China wants only the FEA stockpile (in reply to
                                    Embassy’s telegram No. 10, January 5, 11 a.m.) at Calcutta.
                                    India–Burma Theatre has been so advised by radio.”</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>[Johnson] <lb/>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Josselyn</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>